Lynndie England testified as she pleaded guilty to seven abuse-related charges.
The reduced charges carry a maximum sentence of 11 years.
A female US soldier accused of abusing Iraqi detainees at the Abu Ghraib prison pleaded guilty to several charges at a court-martial at Fort Hood, Texas.
Pfc. Lynndie R. England, the woman seen holding an Iraqi prisoner on a leash in the iconic photo from the Abu Ghraib prison, pleaded guilty to seven charges stemming from prisoner abuse.
She faces up to 6 1/2 years in prison if convicted of conspiracy, maltreating detainees and dereliction of duty.
